  "title": "Accounting Intern",
  "description": "<p>An Accounting Intern supports the finance department with daily tasks, including data entry, account reconciliation, accounts payable/receivable, and financial reporting</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Data Entry & Bookkeeping:</strong> Perform data entry, maintain accurate financial records, and update accounting files.</li><li><strong>Financial Reporting:</strong> Assist in preparing, analyzing, and reviewing financial reports and statements.</li><li><strong>Accounts Payable/Receivable:</strong> Process invoices, follow up on payments, and manage expense reports.</li><li><strong>Reconciliation & Auditing:</strong> Assist with bank reconciliations, internal audits, and compliance checks.</li><li><strong>Administrative Support:</strong> Maintain filing systems, research discrepancies, and assist with month-end/year-end closing processes. </li></ul><p><strong>Required Qualifications & Skills</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Education:</strong> Currently pursuing or recently completed a Bachelor's degree in Accounting, Finance, or Economics.</li><li><strong>Skills:</strong> Strong understanding of basic accounting principles and GAAP.</li><li><strong>Software:</strong> Proficiency in Microsoft Office (especially Excel) and familiarity with accounting software like QuickBooks, Xero, or SAP.</li><li><strong>Attributes:</strong> High attention to detail, strong analytical, organizational, and communication skills.</li><li><strong>Integrity:</strong> Ability to handle confidential financial information with discretion</li></ul>",
